KIA has unveiled its new all-electric version of the Niro at the 5th International Electric Vehicle Expo in Jeju, Korea. The Niro EV features an exclusive radiator grille, futuristic air intake and arrowhead-shaped LED daytime running lights. The vehicle is powered by KIA’s next-generation electric vehicle powertrain, using new production technologies developed specifically for KIA EVs. Equipped with a high-capacity 64 kWh lithium-polymer battery pack, the Niro EV is targeting a zero-emission range of over 380 km on a single charge, or up to 240 km when paired with the 39.2 kWh battery system.   Read: KIA Stinger GT – South African pricing and release details revealed